# English comments in code

All **developer-facing** annotations in source files must be written in **English**:

- Line comments (`#`, `//`, `/* … */`)
- Module, class, and function **docstrings**
- Inline developer notes above blocks of logic

**User-facing copy stays in Russian** (per `AGENTS.md`): templates, error messages shown to learners, quiz/task theory text, achievement titles, CLI `help=` strings for management commands, and seeded content in `task_hints.py` / `task_descriptions.py` / `theory_content.py`.

Identifiers (names of variables, functions, files, CSS classes) remain in English.

When editing a file that still has Russian comments, translate them in the same change.
